    "long_instructions": "### Ramona's Song\r\n\r\n**Define:** Ramona is in a groove and has already added the Reggaeton Beat and Groovy Beat 2 to her song. She's asked you to complete the remix by adding bass, leads, and effects that make the track come to life. Your remix should feel dynamic and layered while letting the beats shine.\r\n\r\n**Prepare:** Listen to how the two beats sound together. Plan what kind of bass, leads, and effects will support their rhythm and energy. Listen to the example below for what this could sound like!\r\n\r\n**Try:** Add a bass, lead, and effect track to Ramona's beats. Use at least two rests to add rhythm or surprise, and include one additional loop to create consistency in your remix.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background:#ebe8f1; border: 0; border-radius: 10px; clear:both; padding: 5px\">\r\n\r\nNeed some help? Try the [<i class=\"fa-solid fa-book\"></i> Docs](#clickable=documentation-button) in the upper-right corner!\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n**Reflect:** Listen to your song and iterate until it sounds the way you want it to. In order to complete this level, your remix must include:\r\n\r\n- At least 2 rests\r\n- At least 1 additional loop\r\n- A bass, lead, and effect track",
